ck IV]]<br />{{small| by [[Robert Wells (composer)|Robert Wells]]}}\n|\n* Maktub<br />{{small| by [[:pt:Marcus Viana|Marcus Viana]]}}\n|\n|}\n\n== Records and achievements ==\n===World record scores===\nAlena currently holds the senior world record for the short program and the total score.\n{{-}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=4 align=center | [[List of highest scores in figure skating#Ladies 3|Ladies' short program]]\n|-\n! Date\n! style=\"width:80px;\" | Score\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n| 6 December 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 85.45\n| [[2019\u201320 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2019\u201320 Grand Prix Final]]\n| Current world record.\n|-\n| 22 November 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 85.04\n| [[2019 NHK Trophy]]\n| \n|-\n\n! colspan=4 align=center | [[List of highest scores in figure skating#Ladies 3|Ladies' total score]]\n|-\n! Date\n! style=\"width:80px;\" | Score\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n| 7 December 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 247.59\n| [[2019\u201320 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2019\u201320 Grand Prix Final]]\n| Current world record. \n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Junior world record scores===\nAlena has set the junior world record scores 2 times under the current +5 / -5 GOE (Grade of Execution) system.\n\n{{-}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=4 align=center | [[List of highest junior scores in figure skating#Short program score 2|Junior ladies' short program]]\n|-\n! Date\n! style=\"width:80px;\" | Score\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n| 6 December 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 76.32\n| [[2018\u201319 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2018\u201319 JGP Final]]\n| Current junior world record.\n|-\n! colspan=4 align=center | [[List of highest junior scores in figure skating#Free program score 2|Junior ladies' free program]]\n|-\n! Date\n! style=\"width:80px;\" | Score\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n| 1 September 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 132.42\n| [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Austria|2018 JGP Austria]]\n| This record was later broken by [[Alexandra Trusova]] at [[ISU Junior Grand Prix in Lithuania|2018 JGP Lithuania]]\n|}\n{{-}}\n\n===Historical world record scores===\n'''Note:''' Because of the introduction of the new +5 / -5 GOE (Grade of Execution) system which replaced the previous +3 / -3 GOE system, ISU has decided that all statistics start from zero for the season 2018-19. All previous records are now historical.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.isu.org/statistics |title=Statistics including Personal Best/Season Best information |publisher=[[International Skating Union]] |accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{-}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=4 align=center | [[List of highest historical junior scores in figure skating#Short program score 2|Historical junior ladies' short program]]\n|-\n! Date\n! style=\"width:80px;\" | Score\n! Event\n! Note\n|-\n| 7 December 2017\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 71.65\n| [[2017\u201318 Grand Prix of Figure Skating Final|2017\u201318 JGP Final]]\n| Kostornaia broke [[Alina Zagitova]]'s record from December 2016. \n|}\n{{-}}\n\n== Competitive highlights ==\n\n[[File:Photos \u2013 Junior World Championships 2018 \u2013 Ladies (Medalists) (1).jpg|thumb|260px|Kostornaia (left) with [[Alexandra Trusova]] (center) and [[Mako Yamashita]] (right) at the [[2018 World Junior Figure Skating Championships|2018 World Junior Championships]] podium]]\n\n''GP: [[ISU Grand Prix|Grand Prix]]''; ''JGP: [[ISU Junior Grand Prix|Junior Grand Prix]]''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #ffdead; \" colspan=6 align=center | International<ref name=\"ISU-AK\" />\n|-\n! Event\n! [[2016\u201317 figure skating season|16\u201317]]\n! [[2017\u201318 figure skating season|17\u201318]]\n! [[2018\u201319 figure skating season|18\u201319]]\n! [[2019\u201320 figure skating season|19\u201320]]\n|-\n| align=left | [[World Figure Skating Championships|Worlds]] || || || || C\n|-\n| align=left 